on us and on our children. <MILESTONE N="26"> Then relea&s;ed he Ba|rabbas to them, and having &s;courged Je&s;us, he delivered <HI>him</HI> to be crucified.</P>
<P><MILESTONE N="27"> <NOTE N="&sect;" PLACE="foot"><HI>Mark</HI> xv. 16. <HI>John</HI> xix. 2.</NOTE> Then the &s;oldiers of the governor taking Je|&s;us into the common hall, gathered to him the 
