over all the earth, unto the ninth hour. <MILESTONE N="46"> And about the ninth hour, Je&s;us cried with a loud voice, &s;aying, <NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot"><HI>P&s;alm</HI> xxii. 1.</NOTE> Eli, Eli, lama &s;abachthanni? That is, My God, my God, why ha&s;t thou for&s;aken me? 
<MILESTONE N="47"> Some of them that &s;tood there hearing <HI>it,</HI> &s;aid, 
He calleth Elijah. <MILESTONE N="48"> <NOTE N="&Dagger;" PLACE="foot"><HI>John</HI> xix. 28.</NOTE> And immediately one of them running and taking a &s;ponge filled <HI>it</HI> with vinegar, and putting <HI>it</HI> on a cane, gave him to 
