<DIV2 N="Mark" TYPE="book">
<PB REF="023976_0142_0FC2A17726017A18">
<HEAD>NOTES ON THE Go&s;pel according to St. MARK.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="outline">
<LIST>
<HEAD>THIS CONTAINS,</HEAD>
<ITEM>I. THE Beginning of the Go&s;pel:
<LIST>
<ITEM><HI>a.</HI> John prepares the Way, C. i. 1&mdash;8</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>b.</HI> Baptizes Je&s;us, who is proclaimed the Son of GOD, 9&mdash;11</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>c.</HI> Tempted of Satan, &s;erved by Angels, 12&mdash;13</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
<ITEM>II. The Go&s;pel it&s;elf:
<LIST>
<ITEM><HI>A.</HI> In Galilee; where we may ob&s;erve three Periods:
<LIST>
<ITEM><HI>a.</HI> After John was ca&s;t into Pri&s;on:
<LIST>
<ITEM>In general:
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. The Place and Matter of his Preaching, 14&mdash;15</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. The Calling of &s;everal of the Apo&s;tles, 16&mdash;20</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
<ITEM>In particular:
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. Actions not cen&s;ured by his Adver&s;aries:
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. He teaches with Authority, 21&mdash;22</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. Cures the Demoniac, 23&mdash;28</ITEM>
<ITEM>3. Heals many Sick, 29&mdash;34</ITEM>
<ITEM>4. Prays, 35</ITEM>
<ITEM>5. Teaches every where, 36&mdash;39</ITEM>
<ITEM>6. Clean&s;es the Leper, 40&mdash;45</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
<ITEM>2. Actions cen&s;ured by them:
<LIST>
<ITEM>Here occur,
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. The Paralytic forgiven and healed, C. ii. 1&mdash;12</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. The Call of Levi, and eating with Publicans and Sinners, 13&mdash;17</ITEM>
<ITEM>3. The Que&s;tion concerning Fa&s;ting an&s;wered, 18&mdash;22</ITEM>
<ITEM>4. The Ears of Corn plucked, 23&mdash;28</ITEM>
<ITEM>5. The withered Hand re&s;tored; Snares laid, C. iii. 1&mdash;6</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
<ITEM>3. Our LORD's Retirement: 7&mdash;12
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. At the Sea,</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. In the Mountain, where the Apo&s;tles are called, 13&mdash;19</ITEM>
<ITEM>3. In the Hou&s;e, where after refuting the Bla&s;phemy of the Phari&s;ees, He &s;hews who are his Mother and his Brethren, 20&mdash;35</ITEM>
<ITEM>4. In the Ship; various Parables, C. iv. 1&mdash;34</ITEM>
<ITEM>5. On the Sea, and beyond it, 35&mdash;41</ITEM>
<ITEM>C. v. 1&mdash;20</ITEM>
<ITEM><PB N="144" REF="023976_0143_0FC2A1790481ABD8">
6. On this Side the Sea: Again: Jairus, and the Woman with the Flux of Blood, 21&mdash;43</ITEM>
<ITEM>7. At Nazareth: His Countrymen offended, C. vi. 1&mdash;6</ITEM>
<ITEM>8. The Apo&s;tles &s;ent forth, 7&mdash;13</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>b.</HI> After John was put to Death:
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. Herod's hearing of Je&s;us, and Judgment of Him. 14&mdash;29</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. Chri&s;t's retiring with his Apo&s;tles, now returned, 30&mdash;32</ITEM>
<ITEM>3. The Earne&s;tne&s;s of the People; Chri&s;t's Compa&s;&s;ion; five thou&s;and fed, 33&mdash;44</ITEM>
<ITEM>4. His walking on the Sea, 45&mdash;52</ITEM>
<ITEM>5. He heals many in the Land of Genne&s;aret 53&mdash;56</ITEM>
<ITEM>6. And teaches what defiles a Man; C. vii. 1&mdash;23</ITEM>
<ITEM>7. A Devil ca&s;t out in the Coa&s;ts of Tyre and Sidon 24&mdash;30</ITEM>
<ITEM>8. At the Sea of Galilee, the Deaf and Dumb healed; four thou&s;and fed, 31&mdash;37</ITEM>
<ITEM>C. viii. 1&mdash;9</ITEM>
<ITEM>9. He comes into the Parts of Dalmanutha, and an&s;wers concerning the Sign from Heaven, 10&mdash;13</ITEM>
<ITEM>10. In the Ship, He warns them of evil Leaven, 14&mdash;21</ITEM>
<ITEM>11. At Beth&s;aida, heals the Sick, 22&mdash;26</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>c.</HI> After he was acknowledged to be the Son of GOD:
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. Peter confe&s;&s;ing Him, He enjoins his Di&s;ciples Si|lence; foretels his Pa&s;&s;ion; reproves Peter; ex|horts to follow Him, 27</ITEM>
<ITEM>C. ix. 1</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. Is transfigured; ca&s;ts out a Devil; foretels his Pa&s;&s;ion, 2&mdash;32</ITEM>
<ITEM>3. Reproves and in&s;tructs his Di&s;ciples, 33&mdash;50</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>B.</HI> In Judea:
<LIST>
<ITEM><HI>a.</HI> In the Borders, C. x. 1
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. He treats of Divorce, 2&mdash;12</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. Of little Children, 13&mdash;16</ITEM>
<ITEM>3. Of entering into Life, and of the Danger of Riches, 17&mdash;31</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>b.</HI> In his Way to the City,
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. He foretels his Pa&s;&s;ion a third Time, 32&mdash;34</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. An&s;wers James and John, and in&s;tructs them all, 35&mdash;45</ITEM>
<ITEM>3. At Jericho, gives Sight to Bartimeus, 46&mdash;52</ITEM>
<ITEM>4. At Jeru&s;alem, C. xi. 1</ITEM>
</LIST>
<LIST>
<ITEM><HI>a.</HI> His Royal Entry, 2&mdash;11</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>b.</HI> The Day after,
<LIST>
<ITEM>the Fig-tree cur&s;ed, 12&mdash;14</ITEM>
<ITEM>the Temple purged, 15&mdash;19</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>c.</HI> The Day after that,
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. Near the Fig-tree, He &s;hews the Power of Faith, 20&mdash;26</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. In the Temple,
<LIST>
<ITEM>1. His Authority vindicated, 27&mdash;33</ITEM>
<ITEM>2. The Parable of the wicked Hu&s;bandmen, C. xii. 1&mdash;12</ITEM>
<ITEM>3. Of paying Tribute to Ce&s;ar, 13&mdash;17</ITEM>
<ITEM>4. Of the Re&s;urrection, 18&mdash;27</ITEM>
<ITEM>5. Of the great Commandment, 28&mdash;34</ITEM>
<ITEM>6. Of David's Lord, 35&mdash;37</ITEM>
<ITEM>7. He warns the People of the Scribes, 38&mdash;40</ITEM>
<ITEM>8. Commends the poor Widow, 41&mdash;44</ITEM>
</LIST></ITEM>
