<DIV5 TYPE="commentary">
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<PB N="159" REF="023976_0158_0FC2A1C1B0CF8B60">
<P><LABEL>V. 2.</LABEL> <HI>There met him a man with an unclean &s;pirit</HI>&mdash;St. <HI>Matthew</HI> men|tions Two. Probably this, &s;o particularly &s;poken of here was the mo&s;t remarkably fierce and ungovernable.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<P><LABEL>V. 9.</LABEL> <HI>Man me Is <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">gion; for we are many</HI>&mdash;But all the&s;e &s;eem to have been under one Commander, who accordingly &s;peaks all along, both for them and him&s;elf.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<PB N="160" REF="023976_0159_0FC2A1C332E51D20">
<P><LABEL>V. 15.</LABEL> <HI>And they were afraid</HI>&mdash;It is not improbable they might otherwi&s;e have offered &s;ome Rudene&s;s if not Violence.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<P><LABEL>V. 19.</LABEL> <HI>Tell them how great things the Lord hath done for thee</HI>&mdash;This was peculiarly needful there, where <HI>Chri&s;t</HI> did not go in Per&s;on.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<P><LABEL>V. 20.</LABEL> <HI>He publi&s;hed in Decapolis</HI>&mdash;Not only at Home, but in all that Country where <HI>Je&s;us</HI> Him&s;elf did not come.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<P><LABEL>V. 22.</LABEL> <HI>One of the rulers of the &s;ynagogus</HI>&mdash;To regulate the Affairs of every Synagogue, there was a Council of grave Men. Over the&s;e was a Pre&s;ident, who was termed <HI>The Ruler of the Synagogue.</HI> Some|times there was no more than one Ruler in a Synagogue.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<PB N="161" REF="023976_0160_0FC2A1C6F7E2CEF8">
<P><LABEL>V. 37.</LABEL> <HI>John, the brother of James</HI>&mdash;When St. <HI>Mark</HI> wrote, not long after our LORD's A&s;cen&s;ion, the Memory of St. <HI>James,</HI> lately beheaded, was &s;o fre&s;h, that his Name was more known than that of <HI>Iobn</HI> him&s;elf.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<PB N="162" REF="023976_0161_0FC2A1C8CAD64EA8">
<P><LABEL>V. 40.</LABEL> Them that were with him&mdash;Peter, James, <HI>and</HI> John.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<P><LABEL>V. 43.</LABEL> <HI>He charged them th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> man &s;hould know it</HI>&mdash;That He might avoid every Appearance of Vain glory, might prevent too great a Concour&s;e of People, and might not farther enrage the Scribes and Phari&s;ees again&s;t Him; the Time for his Death, and for the full Manife&s;tation of his Glory, b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ing not yet come. <HI>He commanded &s;omething &s;hould be given her to eat</HI>&mdash;So that when either natural or &s;pi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">tual Life is re&s;tored, even by immediate Miracle, all proper Means are to be u&s;ed in order to pre&s;erve it.</P>
</DIV6>
