<DIV5 TYPE="commentary">
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<PB N="184" REF="023976_0183_0FC2A227EC11FB80">
<P><LABEL>V. 1.</LABEL> <HI>To Bethphage and Bethany, at the mount of Olives</HI>&mdash;The Limits of <HI>Bethany</HI> reached to the Mount of <HI>Olives</HI> and joined to tho&s;e of <HI>Bethphage. Bethphage</HI> was Part of the Suburbs of <HI>Jeru|&s;alem,</HI> and reached from the Mount of <HI>Olives</HI> to the Walls of the City. Our LORD was now come to the Place where the Boundaries of <HI>Bethany</HI> and <HI>Bethphage</HI> met.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<P><LABEL>V. 13.</LABEL> <HI>For it was not a &s;ea&s;on of figs</HI>&mdash;It was not (as we &s;ay) a <HI>good year</HI> for Figs; at lea&s;t not for that early Sort, which alone was ripe &s;o &s;oon in the Spring. </P>
<P>If we render the Words, <HI>It was not the &s;ea&s;on of figs,</HI> that is, the Time of gathering them in, it may mean, <HI>The &s;ea&s;on was not yet:</HI> And &s;o (inclo&s;ing the Words in a Parenthe&s;is, <HI>And coming to it, he found nothing but leaves</HI>) it may refer to the former Part of the Sentence, and may be con&s;idered as the Rea&s;on of <HI>Chri&s;t</HI>'s going to &s;ee, Whether there were any Figs on this Tree. Some who al&s;o read that Clau&s;e in a Parenthe&s;is, tran&s;late the following Words, <HI>For where he was,</HI> it was <HI>the &s;ea&s;on of figs.</HI> And it is certain, this Meaning of the Words &s;uits be&s;t with the great De&s;ign of the Parable, which was to reprove the <HI>Jewi&s;h</HI> Church for its Unfruitfulne&s;s at that very <HI>Sea&s;on,</HI> when Fruit might be&s;t be expected from them.</P>
<P>If we render the Words, <HI>It was not the &s;ea&s;on of figs,</HI> that is, the Time of gathering them in, it may mean, <HI>The &s;ea&s;on was not yet:</HI> And &s;o (inclo&s;ing the Words in a Parenthe&s;is, <HI>And coming to it, he found nothing but leaves</HI>) it may refer to the former Part of the <PB N="185" REF="023976_0184_0FC2A22B70F28C50">Sentence, and may be con&s;idered as the Rea&s;on of <HI>Chri&s;t</HI>'s going to &s;ee, Whether there were any Figs on this Tree. Some who al&s;o read that Clau&s;e in a Parenthe&s;is, tran&s;late the following Words, <HI>For where he was,</HI> it was <HI>the &s;ea&s;on of figs.</HI> And it is certain, this Meaning of the Words &s;uits be&s;t with the great De&s;ign of the Parable, which was to reprove the <HI>Jewi&s;h</HI> Church for its Unfruitfulne&s;s at that very <HI>Sea&s;on,</HI> when Fruit might be&s;t be expected from them.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<P><LABEL>V. 16.</LABEL> <HI>He &s;uffered not that any &s;hould carry a ve&s;&s;el thro' the temple</HI>&mdash;So &s;trong Notions had our LORD, of even relative Holine&s;s! And of the Regard due to tho&s;e Places (as well as Times) that are peculiarly dedicated to GOD.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<P><LABEL>V. 18.</LABEL> <HI>They feared him</HI>&mdash;That is, they were afraid to take Him by Violence, left it &s;hould rai&s;e a Tumult: <HI>becau&s;e all the people was a&s;toni&s;hed at his teaching</HI>&mdash;Both at the Excellence of his Doc|trine, and at the Maje&s;ty and Authority with which He taught.</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<P><LABEL>V. 22.</LABEL> <HI>Have faith in God</HI>&mdash;And who could find Fault, if the Creator and Proprietor of all Things, were to de&s;troy by a &s;ingle Word of his Mouth, a thou&s;and of his inanimate Creatures, were it only to imprint this important Le&s;&s;on more, deeply, on one im|mortal Spirit?</P>
</DIV6>
<DIV6 TYPE="note">
<PB N="186" REF="023976_0185_0FC2A22F31C800D8">
<P><LABEL>V. 25.</LABEL> <HI>When ye &s;tand praying</HI>&mdash;Standing was their u&s;ual Po&s;ture when they prayed. <HI>Forgive</HI>&mdash;And on this Condition, <HI>ye &s;hall have</HI> whatever you a&s;k, <HI>without wrath or doubting.</HI></P>
</DIV6>
