<MILESTONE N="11"> This was the Lord's doing, and it is marvellous 
in our eyes. <MILESTONE N="12"> And they &s;ought to &s;eize him, but feared the multitude; for they knew he had &s;poken the parable again&s;t them; and leaving him, they went away.</P>
<P><MILESTONE N="13"> <NOTE N="&Dagger;" PLACE="foot"><HI>Mat.</HI> xxii. 15. <HI>Luke</HI> xx. 20.</NOTE> And they &s;end to him certain of the Phari|&s;ees, and of the Herodians, to catch him in <HI>his</HI> di&s;|cour&s;e. 
And they coming &s;ay to him, Ma&s;ter, we know that thou art true, and care&s;t for no man; for thou regarde&s;t not the per&s;on of men, but teache&s;t the way of God in truth. <MILESTONE N="14"> Is it law|ful 
