Have ye here any meat? <MILESTONE N="42"> And they gave him a 
piece of a broiled fi&s;h and of an honeycomb. <MILESTONE N="43"> And he took <HI>it,</HI> and ate before them.</P>
<P><MILESTONE N="44"> And he &s;aid to them, The&s;e <HI>are</HI> the words which I &s;peak to you, being yet with you, that all things written in the law of Mo&s;es, and the pro|phets,
<PB N="318" REF="023976_0317_0FC2CB2D12486B80">and the p&s;alms concerning me, mu&s;t be ful|filled. 
<MILESTONE N="45"> Then opened he their under&s;tanding, to 
under&s;tand the &s;criptures, <MILESTONE N="46"> And &s;aid to them, Thus it is written, and thus it behoved Chri&s;t to &s;uffer, and to ri&s;e from the dead the third day: 
